# Frontend submodule git workflow

This Bedrock repo (`site/`) tracks `web/frontend` as a **git submodule**. Never commit frontend source files from the parent repo.

## 1. Frontend changes (submodule only)

All React/Vite work lives in `web/frontend`. Commit and push there first:

```bash
cd web/frontend
git add .
git commit -m "Descriptive message"
git push
```

- Do **not** add `web/frontend/src/**` (or other frontend paths) in the Bedrock root commit.
- Finish and push the submodule commit before updating the parent pointer.

## 2. Bedrock pointer (parent repo only)

After the submodule is pushed, record the new SHA in Bedrock:

```bash
cd ../..   # repo root (from web/frontend)
git add web/frontend
git commit -m "Update frontend submodule reference"
git push
```

The parent commit should only change the `web/frontend` submodule entry (plus any separate Bedrock/PHP changes in their own commits).

## When the user asks to commit

1. Commit in `web/frontend` with a message that describes the frontend work.
2. If they want the full deploy workflow (or said “push”), push the submodule, then update and push the parent pointer.
3. Keep PHP/plugin (`web/app/plugins/headless-core/`, `composer.json`, etc.) commits in the Bedrock repo separate from frontend source commits.

## Dirty submodule warning

If `git status` at the repo root shows `m web/frontend`, there are uncommitted changes inside the submodule. Commit (or discard) them in `web/frontend` before relying on a clean submodule reference.
